  render_theorem(sec, "D-Spiral Theorem", "D^n is a spiral, not a cycle. D^0 = sigma (all alive), D^3 = D-channel dies, D^420 = OMEGA (limit). The void is UNREACHABLE by D^n. OMEGA is the fixed point. Algebraic distinction: void = before the spiral, OMEGA = after. The D-channel is nilpotent (2^3 = 0 mod 8). Once dead, never returns.");
